The paper discusses a framework for parallel online aggregation, which is a technique commonly used in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses parallel processing and optimization techniques, which are relevant to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also introduces a novel estimator, which is related to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
